The paper proposes a framework for learning representations using Auto-Encoding Variational Bayes (AEVB) and kernel-based measures of independence to enforce structural constraints. This approach is relevant to a wide range of machine learning problems, including learning invariant and interpretable representations, as well as applications to single-cell RNA sequencing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are those related to machine learning and data analysis, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
